00:51:23,600 --> 00:51:26,398
l bet she's still got
that silver dollar.

499
00:51:29,120 --> 00:51:30,712
Whatever happened to her?

500
00:51:32,240 --> 00:51:33,832
She growed up.

501
00:51:34,880 --> 00:51:36,950
She was just a girl then, really.

502
00:51:39,400 --> 00:51:40,958
Let me help you with that.

503
00:51:42,440 --> 00:51:45,113
Why didn't you ever marry her
after your wife died?

504
00:51:47,600 --> 00:51:49,318
She was already married.

505
00:51:54,640 --> 00:51:57,598
Her and her husband was young
and miserable with one another...

506
00:51:57,880 --> 00:51:59,996
...like so many
young married folks are.

507
00:52:00,720 --> 00:52:03,314
l thought they'd change
with some age...

508
00:52:03,720 --> 00:52:05,472
...but it didn'tturn out that way.

509
00:52:05,760 --> 00:52:08,354
ls being married always so miserable?
Not really.

510
00:52:08,920 --> 00:52:11,195
About 80 percent of the time,
l guess.

511
00:52:13,840 --> 00:52:16,912
We ought to go to
a real fshing tank next year.

512
00:52:17,200 --> 00:52:20,397
lt don't do to think
about things like that too much.

513
00:52:22,280 --> 00:52:25,033
lf she was here,
l'd probably be just as crazy now...

514
00:52:25,320 --> 00:52:27,959
...as l was then
in about five minutes.

515
00:52:28,600 --> 00:52:30,238
Ain'tthat ridiculous?

516
00:52:32,560 --> 00:52:34,391
No, it ain't really.

517
00:52:34,680 --> 00:52:38,673
Being crazy about a woman like her
is always the right thing to do.

518
00:52:40,640 --> 00:52:44,110
Being a decrepit old bag of bones,
that's what's ridiculous.

519
00:52:44,520 --> 00:52:45,999
Getting old.

520
00:52:56,560 --> 00:53:01,236
Talk to her please, Mr. Sun

521
00:53:03,800 --> 00:53:08,669
Speak to her, Mr. Rainbow

522
00:53:10,720 --> 00:53:15,589
And take her under your branches

523
00:53:17,560 --> 00:53:20,358
Mr. Tree

524
00:53:25,760 --> 00:53:30,629
Whisper to her, Mr. Wind

525
00:53:36,040 --> 00:53:37,758
l'm glad l wasn't on fre.

526
00:53:38,040 --> 00:53:41,077
l'd have burned to death
before you got one button undone.

527
00:53:41,360 --> 00:53:43,351
l'm going to get a drink of water.

528
00:53:51,120 --> 00:53:54,237
l wondered where you went.
Annie Annie asleep?

529
00:54:08,840 --> 00:54:11,229
Nice. You a virgin?

530
00:54:12,560 --> 00:54:13,834
Guess l am.

531
00:54:15,160 --> 00:54:15,990
Too bad.

532
00:54:17,480 --> 00:54:20,153
l don't want to be, though.
l don't blame you.

533
00:54:20,840 --> 00:54:22,512
Come see me when you're not.

534
00:54:46,440 --> 00:54:49,955
Why don't we just go someplace?
l'm sick and tired of this town.

535
00:54:50,240 --> 00:54:52,629
You're the only friend l got.
You mean, go and stay gone?

536
00:54:52,920 --> 00:54:54,319
No, l don't know.

537
00:54:55,760 --> 00:54:58,149
Hey, we go to Mexico.
Be back sometime Monday.

538
00:54:58,680 --> 00:55:01,638
Would the pickup make it?
Yeah. How much money you got?

539
00:55:01,880 --> 00:55:03,074
Thirty bucks about.

540
00:55:03,360 --> 00:55:05,954
Well, l got 40.
We can make it. Come on!

541
00:55:08,040 --> 00:55:09,155
You guys want

542
00:55:09,760 --> 00:55:11,637
Where are you going?
Mexico.

543
00:55:11,880 --> 00:55:12,630
Where?

544
00:55:19,160 --> 00:55:22,277
Better come with us, Sam.
We're headed for the valley.

545
00:55:22,800 --> 00:55:24,472
Where did you say?
Mexico.

546
00:55:24,800 --> 00:55:26,870
lt's about the wildest.
All the way down.

547
00:55:27,520 --> 00:55:31,308
You going all the way to Mexico
tonight in this old heap ofjunk?

548
00:55:31,600 --> 00:55:32,749
My God!

549
00:55:33,040 --> 00:55:35,998
Reckon the town will get along
without us till Monday?

550
00:55:36,240 --> 00:55:36,990
l reckon.

551
00:55:37,280 --> 00:55:39,794
lf l was young enough,
l'd go with you.

552
00:55:40,400 --> 00:55:42,595
Need any money?
No, we got plenty.

553
00:55:43,320 --> 00:55:46,676
Well, you'd better take some
for some insurance.

554
00:55:47,440 --> 00:55:50,398
Take money below that border,
it sort of melts.

555
00:55:50,680 --> 00:55:51,874
Thanks, Sam.

556
00:55:52,680 --> 00:55:55,114
Try not to drink too much
of that buggy water.

557
00:55:55,400 --> 00:55:58,198
We'll just drink beer and tequila.

558
00:55:59,000 --> 00:56:02,470
You catch the clap, you'll wish
you hadn't drunk nothing.

559
00:56:14,600 --> 00:56:15,715
Oh, well.

560
00:56:16,440 --> 00:56:17,509
We'll see you.

561
00:56:17,800 --> 00:56:19,313
So long!

562
00:56:49,680 --> 00:56:50,999
Hey, wake up!

563
00:56:51,400 --> 00:56:52,435
We're back.

564
00:56:54,400 --> 00:56:57,153
My stomach don't feel so good.
Got any more Tums?

565
00:56:57,520 --> 00:57:00,956
You ate them all
before we got to San Antonio.

566
00:57:02,200 --> 00:57:05,510
Genevieve will have something.
My stomach don't feel so good.

567
00:57:08,440 --> 00:57:09,236
Closed.

568
00:57:09,720 --> 00:57:11,039
Closed?

569
00:57:13,160 --> 00:57:15,151
l ain't never seen her closed before.

570
00:57:15,440 --> 00:57:17,476
No, not even for Christmas.

571
00:57:18,920 --> 00:57:22,151
Maybe Sam will have something.
l'm sick.

572
00:57:44,000 --> 00:57:45,638
Well, it ain't that early.

573
00:57:46,280 --> 00:57:47,872
Must be some kind of holiday.

574
00:57:48,160 --> 00:57:50,276
Sam don't close on holidays.

575
00:57:50,560 --> 00:57:52,755
Maybe he had to go someplace.

576
00:57:56,320 --> 00:57:58,117
Let's go askAndy.

577
00:58:11,080 --> 00:58:13,594
Somebody will steal the town.
Where is everybody?

578
00:58:14,080 --> 00:58:15,718
Asleep.
Everybody that's got sense.

579
00:58:16,000 --> 00:58:18,036
Why'd Sam close the cafe?

580
00:58:18,560 --> 00:58:20,869
Y'all been gone, ain't you?

581
00:58:21,480 --> 00:58:23,038
Gone to Mexico.

582
00:58:23,480 --> 00:58:25,277
You don't know about it.
What?

583
00:58:25,560 --> 00:58:27,198
Sam died yesterday morning.

584
00:58:29,040 --> 00:58:29,916
Died?

585
00:58:30,200 --> 00:58:31,838
Quite a blow.

586
00:58:32,120 --> 00:58:35,396
Keeled over one of
the snooker tables, had a stroke.

587
00:58:36,440 --> 00:58:38,192
Sam the Lion?

588
00:58:39,520 --> 00:58:40,430
Sam's dead.

589
00:58:40,760 --> 00:58:42,398
He was quite a fellow.

590
00:58:44,400 --> 00:58:47,233
He had his own way of doing things,
that's for sure.

591
00:58:48,920 --> 00:58:51,639
They found his will.
Craziest thing you ever heard.

592
00:58:52,480 --> 00:58:56,234
He left you the pool hall, Sonny.
What do you think about that?

593
00:58:57,800 --> 00:58:59,791
He left Genevieve the cafe.

594
00:59:00,080 --> 00:59:02,992
That's the only thing he done
that made any sense.

595
00:59:03,480 --> 00:59:05,994
Leftthe picture show
to old Miss Mosey.

596
00:59:06,280 --> 00:59:09,670
Hell, she's too far gone
to even run a popcorn machine.

597
00:59:10,240 --> 00:59:11,958
And the craziest thing of all...

598
00:59:12,240 --> 00:59:16,028
...he left $1000 to Joe Bob Blanton,
the preacher's boy.

599
00:59:16,640 --> 00:59:18,756
Beats all l ever heard of.

600
00:59:19,160 --> 00:59:21,515
He could just as easily
left that to me.

601
00:59:21,800 --> 00:59:25,270
l deserve it at least as much
as that ignorant little bastard.

602
00:59:26,880 --> 00:59:28,791
Anyhow, it's done.

603
00:59:29,080 --> 00:59:30,957
They're burying him tomorrow.

604
01:01:47,000 --> 01:01:48,115
Come in.

605
01:02:02,720 --> 01:02:04,790
l love you.
l love you too.

606
01:02:34,880 --> 01:02:36,279
Oh, Duane, hurry.

607
01:03:10,240 --> 01:03:11,559
What's wrong, honey?

608
01:03:13,480 --> 01:03:14,833
l don't know.

609
01:03:16,480 --> 01:03:18,789
That tickles.
l can't stand to be tickled.

610
01:03:27,840 --> 01:03:29,717
Aren't you gonna do it?

611
01:03:30,840 --> 01:03:32,034
l don't know what's wrong.

612
01:03:32,280 --> 01:03:35,397
How could anything be wrong?
Just go on and do it.

613
01:03:39,440 --> 01:03:41,078
What's the matter with you?

614
01:03:42,000 --> 01:03:43,752
l don't know.
Something's happened.

615
01:03:44,000 --> 01:03:46,753
Get off a minute!
You mightfall and mash me.

616
01:03:47,040 --> 01:03:48,314
l don't know what happened.

617
01:03:49,080 --> 01:03:51,674
l knew you couldn't do it.
Now l'll never not be a virgin!

618
01:03:51,920 --> 01:03:53,876
What do we say?
The whole class knows.

619
01:03:54,160 --> 01:03:56,469
l want to cry.
You're the meanest boy l ever saw.

620
01:03:56,720 --> 01:03:58,756
My mother was dead right about you.

621
01:03:59,880 --> 01:04:00,995
l don't know what happened.

622
01:04:01,280 --> 01:04:04,192
Don't go out there!
We haven't had time to do it.

623
01:04:04,440 --> 01:04:07,000
l don't want one soul to know.
You better not tell.

624
01:04:08,360 --> 01:04:10,078
You just pretend it was wonderful!

625
01:04:10,360 --> 01:04:12,032
l don't know what happened.

626
01:04:13,560 --> 01:04:15,551
lf you say that again,
l'll bite you!

627
01:04:35,080 --> 01:04:37,275
Tell us about it, Jacy.
What was it like?

628
01:04:40,280 --> 01:04:42,555
l just can't describe it.

629
01:04:42,960 --> 01:04:45,394
l just can't describe it in words.

630
01:04:53,520 --> 01:04:56,717
Texas, our Texas

631
01:04:56,960 --> 01:05:00,999
All hail the mighty state

632
01:05:01,560 --> 01:05:04,677
Texas, our Texas

633
01:05:04,920 --> 01:05:08,833
So wonderful, so great

634
01:05:09,440 --> 01:05:12,716
Largest and grandest

635
01:05:12,960 --> 01:05:16,839
Withstanding every test

636
01:05:17,120 --> 01:05:20,908
O empire wide and glorious

637
01:05:21,160 --> 01:05:25,278
You stand supremely blessed

638
01:05:25,840 --> 01:05:28,274
God bless you, Texas

639
01:05:28,520 --> 01:05:30,715
l can do it now.
l know l can.

640
01:05:33,600 --> 01:05:38,071
That you may grow
ln power and worth

641
01:05:38,560 --> 01:05:43,429
Throughout the ages on

642
01:06:03,920 --> 01:06:06,992
Quit prissing! l don'tthink
you did it right anyway.

643
01:06:17,080 --> 01:06:18,149
Come on.

644
01:06:28,040 --> 01:06:31,191
lt's your graduation present.
Hope you like it.

645
01:06:40,720 --> 01:06:42,756
l never seen one as nice.

646
01:06:57,080 --> 01:06:58,593
What's on your feeble mind?

647
01:06:58,960 --> 01:07:00,473
Same as it's been.
l want a date.

648
01:07:01,640 --> 01:07:03,517
Why don't you just
go back to Mexico?

649
01:07:03,800 --> 01:07:06,109
l guess girls are easier
to please down there.

650
01:07:06,600 --> 01:07:08,318
Just go with me one more time.

651
01:07:08,560 --> 01:07:09,959
You can at least see me.

652
01:07:10,240 --> 01:07:12,515
Find somebody else to pester.
Got a new boyfriend.

653
01:07:12,760 --> 01:07:14,671
l can't talk to you.
Who?

654
01:07:14,920 --> 01:07:16,399
Bobby Sheen, of course.

655
01:07:18,160 --> 01:07:19,832
You crazy?
l certainly am not.

656
01:07:20,080 --> 01:07:23,550
l guess l wanted to go with him
all along and never realized it.

657
01:07:23,920 --> 01:07:26,309
Maybe we'll see you
in Wichita sometime.

658
01:07:40,280 --> 01:07:42,999
Goddamn it to hell!

659
01:07:54,840 --> 01:07:56,114
l hate to see you go.

660
01:07:56,400 --> 01:07:58,356
Not a goddamn thing
to stay for.

661
01:07:58,760 --> 01:08:01,479
Roughnecks say you can get a job
in Odessa anytime.

662
01:08:02,320 --> 01:08:03,912
Come on back if you don't.

663
01:08:16,800 --> 01:08:18,916
You hear they busted up,
let me know.

664
01:08:52,960 --> 01:08:53,870
Didn't hear you.

665
01:08:55,240 --> 01:08:55,990
Gene home?

666
01:08:56,600 --> 01:08:58,750
No, he and Mama went to the club.

667
01:09:03,800 --> 01:09:05,518
Why are you home
on a Saturday night?

668
01:09:07,760 --> 01:09:09,990
Bobbie Sheen ran off and got married.

669
01:09:12,720 --> 01:09:14,153
Annie Annie Martin.

670
01:09:18,040 --> 01:09:19,234
Want me to turn the TV off?

671
01:09:20,040 --> 01:09:23,669
No, l'm gonna go play pool.
Tell your dad that well came in okay.

672
01:09:25,000 --> 01:09:27,753
l wish l could go to the pool hall.
l've always wanted to.

673
01:09:28,000 --> 01:09:30,878
lt's terrible, the things
girls aren't allowed to do.

674
01:09:32,800 --> 01:09:35,633
Well, hell, come on.
l'll show you the pool hall.

675
01:09:35,920 --> 01:09:37,069
Aren'tthere people there?

676
01:09:37,360 --> 01:09:39,828
lf there are,
they'll be in back asleep now.

677
01:09:40,120 --> 01:09:43,112
Won't bother us.
Got my own key.

678
01:09:44,360 --> 01:09:46,112
Okay, l will then.

679
01:10:01,480 --> 01:10:03,914
Goodness, it sure is dark in here.

680
01:12:22,280 --> 01:12:25,716
What a night! l never thought
something like this would happen.

681
01:12:27,640 --> 01:12:29,358
How about hopping out?

682
01:13:03,200 --> 01:13:05,714
He's just awful!
Why do you fool with him?

683
01:13:05,960 --> 01:13:08,554
Daddy's nicer than him, isn't he?
He sure is.

684
01:13:08,800 --> 01:13:10,711
Your daddy's a very nice man.

685
01:13:10,960 --> 01:13:13,474
l ought to give Abilene hell
instead of him.

686
01:13:13,760 --> 01:13:16,877
Bobby was the last one.
l'm just gonna be an old maid.

687
01:13:17,160 --> 01:13:20,755
That'sjust the way it goes.
You win a few, you lose a few.

688
01:13:21,040 --> 01:13:22,109
What do you do?

689
01:13:22,400 --> 01:13:24,356
Nothing's ever the way
it's supposed to be.

690
01:13:24,640 --> 01:13:26,232
You're right. Come on.

691
01:13:29,880 --> 01:13:33,793
l want to tell you what l've done
has not worked out too well.

692
01:13:34,080 --> 01:13:37,709
l think maybe we better think of
something else for you.

693
01:13:39,440 --> 01:13:42,512
l guess Ruth Popper's got
about as good a setup as anyone.

694
01:13:42,800 --> 01:13:46,475
Why, sure. Sonny's reasonably
good looking and he's young.

695
01:13:46,760 --> 01:13:49,752
Don't you know?
lt's been going on about six months.

696
01:13:50,000 --> 01:13:52,514
l thought you kids knew everything.
That's silly!

697
01:13:52,800 --> 01:13:54,028
She's 40 years old.

698
01:13:54,320 --> 01:13:56,834
So am l, honey.
lt's kind of an itchy age.

699
01:13:57,120 --> 01:13:58,553
Want an orange?

700
01:13:58,840 --> 01:14:00,432
l don't believe it.

701
01:14:01,160 --> 01:14:03,754
Sonny's always wanted to go with me.

702
01:14:08,920 --> 01:14:10,911
Pretty easy shot, sheriff.

703
01:14:19,400 --> 01:14:20,594
Sheriff, we got trouble.

704
01:14:22,600 --> 01:14:25,478
Goddamn you, Monroe!
You made me scratch.

705
01:14:25,760 --> 01:14:29,594
Sorry, sheriff, but Johnny Clarg's
little girl's been kidnapped.

706
01:14:29,880 --> 01:14:32,872
They say the preacher's boy put her
in his car two hours ago.

707
01:14:33,200 --> 01:14:36,988
What the hell? Maybe Joe Bob
just give her a ride home.

708
01:14:37,280 --> 01:14:39,635
Be doing her a favour
in this hot weather.

709
01:14:39,920 --> 01:14:42,434
Who'd want to kidnap Molly Clarg?

710
01:14:42,680 --> 01:14:44,238
l just know she's not home.

711
01:14:44,520 --> 01:14:46,829
They was seen headed toward Olney.

712
01:14:47,120 --> 01:14:49,588
Mrs. Clarg's afraid
that Joe Bob might be...

713
01:14:49,880 --> 01:14:52,917
...gonna molest her or something.

714
01:14:53,160 --> 01:14:54,991
You and some of these boys
come with us.

715
01:14:55,720 --> 01:14:58,712
lf that's the way it is,
no telling what we'll fnd.

716
01:15:24,280 --> 01:15:25,633
Molly!

717
01:15:30,440 --> 01:15:32,396
Get him! Ain't you going to?

718
01:15:32,920 --> 01:15:34,114
Here's my little girl.

719
01:15:34,400 --> 01:15:37,073
He's the one that done it.
Why don't you get him?

720
01:15:37,360 --> 01:15:40,033
lf my husband was here,
he'd kill him dead.

721
01:15:45,480 --> 01:15:48,392
What'd you do to that child?
We know you done something.

722
01:15:48,720 --> 01:15:49,914
Come on.

723
01:15:52,440 --> 01:15:53,714
Filthy!

724
01:15:53,960 --> 01:15:57,748
Here now, grab her.
None of this goddamn frenzy.

725
01:16:01,920 --> 01:16:03,558
lt's the Lord's justice, son.

726
01:16:03,800 --> 01:16:06,030
You'll suffer with the murderer
and the thief.

727
01:16:06,320 --> 01:16:10,029
Sonny, drive that Plymouth to town.
We gotta get this man to jail.

728
01:16:19,720 --> 01:16:22,359
Doctor said he didn't do nothing.
Never had the guts.

729
01:16:22,600 --> 01:16:24,830
Preacher's boy.
Sheriff fgured he done something.

730
01:16:32,360 --> 01:16:35,079
lsn't it terrible, Sonny?
Did you see anything?

731
01:16:35,360 --> 01:16:37,351
Weren't nothing to see
except Mrs. Clarg.

732
01:16:37,600 --> 01:16:40,034
lf she had a gun,
she might've killed us all.

733
01:16:40,320 --> 01:16:41,673
Joe Bob didn't do nothing.

734
01:16:41,960 --> 01:16:45,111
He must've done something.
lt scares me to death.

735
01:16:45,360 --> 01:16:48,432
You never can tell when something
terrible is gonna happen.

736
01:16:49,840 --> 01:16:51,637
lt's okay.
They got him now.

737
01:16:51,920 --> 01:16:53,592
l called you before.

738
01:16:54,640 --> 01:16:55,470
You did?

739
01:16:56,440 --> 01:16:57,589
l felt lonesome.

740
01:16:57,880 --> 01:16:59,871
Thought you might wanna
drive around.

741
01:17:03,200 --> 01:17:05,430
Well, l'm supposed to be someplace.

742
01:17:05,720 --> 01:17:09,315
l'm still a little scared.
Please take me riding.

743
01:17:14,960 --> 01:17:16,188
Where will we drive?

744
01:17:40,680 --> 01:17:41,749
Ever hear from Duane?

745
01:17:42,000 --> 01:17:43,115
Got a postcard.

746
01:17:43,560 --> 01:17:45,949
l really feel sad about that.

747
01:17:47,560 --> 01:17:49,630
He's making 320 a month.
Said he bought a car.

748
01:17:50,640 --> 01:17:54,792
l'll always be a little in love with
Duane. We had too much against us.

749
01:17:55,680 --> 01:17:58,148
lt wasn't easy
being the one to break up.

750
01:18:27,840 --> 01:18:28,716
What?

751
01:19:04,440 --> 01:19:06,271
l don't like to hurry.

752
01:19:07,080 --> 01:19:10,675
Why don't we go to Wichita
and get a motel room?

753
01:19:11,040 --> 01:19:13,235
l'm afraid to.
My folks are watching me.

754
01:19:13,520 --> 01:19:15,511
They know l don't wanna
go to college.

755
01:19:15,800 --> 01:19:18,189
They might think we'll run off
and get married.

756
01:19:20,360 --> 01:19:22,476
We'll do it when it's safe.

757
01:19:23,280 --> 01:19:25,555
We got all summer.

758
01:20:16,920 --> 01:20:18,273
Hey, buddy!

759
01:20:19,840 --> 01:20:20,829
You turned roughneck.

760
01:20:21,120 --> 01:20:23,395
Gotta make a living
so l can keep the pool hall open.

761
01:20:23,680 --> 01:20:24,556
When did you get in?

762
01:20:24,840 --> 01:20:27,354
About 2.
l thought l'd surprise you.

763
01:20:29,200 --> 01:20:30,076
ls this yours?

764
01:20:30,360 --> 01:20:33,750
How about that?
38,000 miles and she runs like new.

765
01:20:34,040 --> 01:20:35,632
Do you want a beer?
Not me.

766
01:20:36,320 --> 01:20:38,515
That's all l eat
for breakfast anymore.

767
01:20:38,800 --> 01:20:40,677
Sure is a nice car.

768
01:20:40,960 --> 01:20:44,555
l like to drive it so much, l thought
l'd just drop home for the weekend.

769
01:20:46,480 --> 01:20:49,392
You can't take too good care
of a car like this.

770
01:20:50,520 --> 01:20:52,078
l wash her every week.

771
01:20:52,360 --> 01:20:53,793
lt looks great.

772
01:20:54,640 --> 01:20:55,595
Hear about Joe Bob?

773
01:20:55,880 --> 01:20:58,030
l always knew he was crazy.

774
01:20:58,320 --> 01:21:01,835
He didn't do nothing, except get her
to take her underpants off.

775
01:21:02,480 --> 01:21:03,993
He's out of jail now.

776
01:21:05,080 --> 01:21:06,877
Are you still screwing
that old lady?

777
01:21:08,240 --> 01:21:10,674
No. Yeah.
l've been kind of busy.

778
01:21:11,480 --> 01:21:13,596
l seen old Leroy last week.

779
01:21:13,920 --> 01:21:16,309
Said you and Jacy
been going together.

780
01:21:17,040 --> 01:21:18,234
We have, a little.

781
01:21:18,520 --> 01:21:21,796
She's been bored, so sometimes
we go eat Mexican food.

782
01:21:22,120 --> 01:21:24,270
l hear that ain't all
you been eating.

783
01:21:25,400 --> 01:21:28,392
Whoever told you that don't know
what he's talking about.

784
01:21:28,800 --> 01:21:30,518
l been going with her.
Why not?

785
01:21:30,760 --> 01:21:33,228
l never said l blamed you for it.

786
01:21:33,920 --> 01:21:36,514
l never thought you'd do that.
l thought we was friends.

787
01:21:36,760 --> 01:21:39,911
We are. What you so mad for?
l never done nothing.

788
01:21:40,200 --> 01:21:41,474
Screwing my girl ain't nothing?

789
01:21:41,760 --> 01:21:42,590
l ain't.

790
01:21:42,840 --> 01:21:45,195
Hell, you ain't!
Well, l ain't.

791
01:21:45,480 --> 01:21:47,118
She's not your girl.
She is!

792
01:21:47,400 --> 01:21:48,674
You don't even live here anymore.

793
01:21:48,960 --> 01:21:51,679
That don't make no difference!
l'm getting her back.

794
01:21:51,920 --> 01:21:53,512
She'll marry me someday.

795
01:21:53,760 --> 01:21:55,796
She won't.
We're meant to get married.

796
01:21:56,080 --> 01:21:57,433
She's off to college soon.

797
01:21:57,720 --> 01:22:00,837
l doubt l'll get to go with her
myself, once she gets off.

798
01:22:01,120 --> 01:22:03,918
l never saw what it could hurt
to go with her this summer.

799
01:22:04,200 --> 01:22:06,509
She'll never marry you.
Don't tell me she won't!

800
01:22:07,520 --> 01:22:09,317
She'd never let you screw her.

801
01:22:09,600 --> 01:22:12,068
l was just seeing how honest you was.

802
01:22:12,360 --> 01:22:15,193
Jacy'd never let you screw her.
You ain'tthat good a cocksman.

803
01:22:16,160 --> 01:22:18,435
You never even screwed Charlene
all that time.

804
01:22:18,800 --> 01:22:19,550
Course l didn't!

805
01:22:19,840 --> 01:22:21,034
You know why?

806
01:22:21,320 --> 01:22:24,232
Because you had the pickup
all the time Saturday night.

807
01:22:24,560 --> 01:22:26,039
Nobody could've screwed
in the time l had.

808
01:22:26,320 --> 01:22:29,073
l could've screwed her in five minutes.
l wouldn't need no pickup.

809
01:22:29,480 --> 01:22:32,438
She only went with you because
you was in the backfiield...

810
01:22:32,720 --> 01:22:34,358
...and l was in the line.

811
01:22:34,600 --> 01:22:36,318
What you talking about?
We was in love.

812
01:22:36,560 --> 01:22:39,518
You was. She likes me as much
as she ever liked you.

813
01:22:40,080 --> 01:22:40,910
That's a lie.

814
01:22:41,160 --> 01:22:42,513
l'll stay with her all night too.

815
01:22:42,760 --> 01:22:44,113
She promised.
You won't.

816
01:22:44,360 --> 01:22:45,395
Why shouldn't l?

817
01:22:45,640 --> 01:22:48,996
She told me you couldn't do it
that time in Wichita Falls.

818
01:23:11,080 --> 01:23:12,399
What happened?

819
01:23:28,200 --> 01:23:31,192
There's a lady in the waiting room.
She sent you this.

820
01:23:34,400 --> 01:23:37,790
May l come in and see you
a little while? Ruth

821
01:23:43,560 --> 01:23:45,073
Could you tell her l'm asleep?

822
01:23:45,760 --> 01:23:46,954
Please?

823
01:23:47,240 --> 01:23:48,468
All right.

824
01:24:13,760 --> 01:24:14,829
That too cold?

825
01:24:15,120 --> 01:24:16,553
No, it's great.

826
01:24:18,360 --> 01:24:20,920
l hear Duane joined the Army.

827
01:24:21,200 --> 01:24:23,031
Good place for him too.

828
01:24:23,320 --> 01:24:25,550
He didn't mean to hit me
with the bottle.

829
01:24:25,840 --> 01:24:28,434
That boy's always had
meanness in him.

830
01:24:29,040 --> 01:24:32,271
Jacy's the kind of girl that
brings out the meanness in a man.

831
01:24:32,560 --> 01:24:34,357
She'sjust like her grandmother.

832
01:24:36,960 --> 01:24:40,475
l hadn't ought to talk about them.
We was all good friends once.

833
01:24:41,520 --> 01:24:43,670
Dan roughnecked with Gene Farrow.

834
01:24:44,560 --> 01:24:47,154
He and Lois used to live
in this one room place...

835
01:24:47,440 --> 01:24:49,158
...over the newspaper office.

836
01:24:49,600 --> 01:24:52,990
Lois couldn't afford a flour sack,
much less a mink.

837
01:24:55,400 --> 01:24:58,233
l've always had
a soft spot for her, though.

838
01:25:00,480 --> 01:25:03,199
l wondered a lot of times
what would've happened...

839
01:25:03,480 --> 01:25:05,948
...if my Dan had made
the strikes that Gene made.

840
01:25:06,240 --> 01:25:08,549
They offered that rig to him fiirst.

841
01:25:12,440 --> 01:25:15,318
Dan Morgan never took a chance
in his life.

842
01:25:16,440 --> 01:25:17,873
Do you wish y'all had made it?

843
01:25:21,760 --> 01:25:24,194
Sure, l wish we'd made it.

844
01:25:26,520 --> 01:25:29,751
l guess the Army won't take me now,
l just got one good eye.

845
01:25:30,040 --> 01:25:32,190
You wanna go to Korea
and get killed?

846
01:25:32,480 --> 01:25:36,519
You ain't got your senses back yet,
what few you ever had.

847
01:25:37,920 --> 01:25:40,195
The cafe won't run itself.
You rest up now.

848
01:25:40,480 --> 01:25:42,596
Here's for the cheeseburger.

849
01:25:42,880 --> 01:25:45,474
l'll bring your change
when l bring your supper.

850
01:26:15,920 --> 01:26:17,273
Come on in.

851
01:26:25,680 --> 01:26:27,591
l was so worried.
l just had to see you.

852
01:26:27,880 --> 01:26:29,438
l've been missing you.

853
01:26:29,720 --> 01:26:32,598
And l'm a lot better than l was.
Here, sit down.

854
01:26:33,240 --> 01:26:36,710
You can't believe how famous we are.
We're all anybody talks about.

855
01:26:37,000 --> 01:26:39,309
Yeah, l guess so.
l want us to get married.

856
01:26:40,840 --> 01:26:41,909
l really do.

857
01:26:42,320 --> 01:26:43,070
Get married?

858
01:26:43,360 --> 01:26:45,396
As soon as you want to.
Don't you want to?

859
01:26:47,960 --> 01:26:51,157
The town will be knocked for a loop.
They'll never forget it.

860
01:26:51,400 --> 01:26:52,799
Ain't you going to college?

861
01:26:53,040 --> 01:26:55,349
l love you,
and that's more important.

862
01:26:57,360 --> 01:26:59,237
You were so dear to fiightfor me.

863
01:26:59,640 --> 01:27:01,232
My folks won't like it
but we'll run off.

864
01:27:01,520 --> 01:27:03,192
They'll kill us.
No, they won't.

865
01:27:03,480 --> 01:27:05,198
They'll kill me.
They'll get over it.

866
01:27:05,480 --> 01:27:07,152
You're working for Daddy now anyway.

867
01:27:07,440 --> 01:27:10,432
Pretty soon, they'll love you
just as much as l do.

868
01:27:13,120 --> 01:27:14,439
Can we?

869
01:27:15,080 --> 01:27:17,992
Sure, l just hope l can see to drive.

870
01:27:18,400 --> 01:27:20,470
Don't you worry.
l can drive.

871
01:27:30,360 --> 01:27:31,918
Don't do that, Sonny.

872
01:27:32,400 --> 01:27:33,753
Why not?

873
01:27:34,040 --> 01:27:36,110
We're man and wife now.
We can do anything.

874
01:27:36,400 --> 01:27:38,709
Not while l'm driving.
l might have a wreck.

875
01:27:39,520 --> 01:27:43,479
Wouldn't it be awful if Mama
and Daddy got the police after us?

876
01:27:43,760 --> 01:27:46,911
They don't even know where we are.
l had to leave them a note.

877
01:27:47,720 --> 01:27:49,631
So they wouldn't be worried
out of their mind.

878
01:27:49,920 --> 01:27:51,319
You shouldn't have done that.

879
01:27:51,560 --> 01:27:53,755
l fgured they'd have
to know sometime.

880
01:27:54,000 --> 01:27:56,070
Well, what could they get us for?

881
01:27:56,360 --> 01:27:59,079
We got a right to get married.
Ain't we?

882
01:27:59,440 --> 01:28:01,078
l guess so.

883
01:28:04,200 --> 01:28:07,192
l wish you didn't have that
stupid eye patch. lt's really creepy.

884
01:28:07,560 --> 01:28:10,154
l can take it off pretty soon.

885
01:28:11,080 --> 01:28:15,358
About two hours will be Lake Texoma.
Have a room to ourself.

886
01:28:15,640 --> 01:28:18,996
My goodness! You're sitting so close,
l can barely drive.

887
01:28:44,920 --> 01:28:46,114
Oh, goodness.

888
01:29:08,640 --> 01:29:09,390
Howdy.

889
01:29:09,640 --> 01:29:11,790
What part of Texas y'all from?
Anarene.

890
01:29:12,080 --> 01:29:13,752
Newlyweds, ain't you?

891
01:29:14,360 --> 01:29:17,591
Y'all better follow me in.
Somebody's looking for you.

892
01:29:17,840 --> 01:29:20,513
We got a right to get married.
How can you arrest us?

893
01:29:20,920 --> 01:29:23,912
l ain't arresting you.
l just want you to come with me.

894
01:29:24,160 --> 01:29:25,718
l don't know what your rights are.

895
01:29:26,000 --> 01:29:27,638
l guess we better follow him.

896
01:29:27,880 --> 01:29:30,269
l'll be heartbroken
if my folks have done this.

897
01:29:35,560 --> 01:29:38,438
You think l worked hard so
my daughter'd end up in a pool hall?

898
01:29:38,880 --> 01:29:41,189
We was gonna get an apartment.
l'll bet!

899
01:29:41,480 --> 01:29:42,515
Where are your car keys?

900
01:29:42,800 --> 01:29:44,870
lt's a hell of a note!

901
01:29:45,120 --> 01:29:47,634
Shut up and take her home.
You bet l will!

902
01:29:47,880 --> 01:29:51,270
You take her car.
As far as l'm concerned, he can walk!

903
01:30:18,720 --> 01:30:21,518
Not much of a wedding night, huh?

904
01:30:21,800 --> 01:30:22,710
Not much of one.

905
01:30:23,000 --> 01:30:26,276
Here. Have a little drink of bourbon.
lt'll pick you up.

906
01:30:26,520 --> 01:30:28,431
Take all of it. l'm gonna drive.

907
01:30:30,840 --> 01:30:32,114
You won't believe this...

908
01:30:32,400 --> 01:30:35,472
...but you're lucky we got you
clear of her quick as we did.

909
01:30:35,880 --> 01:30:38,633
You'd have been better off
staying with Ruth Popper.

910
01:30:38,880 --> 01:30:41,075
Does everybody know about that?

911
01:30:41,360 --> 01:30:42,475
Course!

912
01:30:43,000 --> 01:30:47,118
Sounded like a good deal to me.
Shouldn't let Jacy turn your head.

913
01:30:47,400 --> 01:30:49,277
Well, she's prettier.

914
01:30:50,200 --> 01:30:54,193
l guess l shouldn't have, though.
l guess l treated her terrible.

915
01:30:54,480 --> 01:30:55,799
Guess you did.

916
01:31:15,040 --> 01:31:16,917
Sure weren't out of Texas very long.

917
01:31:17,200 --> 01:31:20,078
Oklahoma's not much
of an improvement.

918
01:31:25,320 --> 01:31:27,072
lt's not the same now.

919
01:31:28,800 --> 01:31:31,712
Nothing's really been right
since Sam the Lion died.

920
01:31:37,160 --> 01:31:38,912
No, it hasn't.

921
01:31:42,480 --> 01:31:44,038
Oh, God.

922
01:31:46,800 --> 01:31:49,360
l get sad if l think of Sam for long.

923
01:31:53,160 --> 01:31:55,116
Did you know he had beautiful hands?

924
01:31:56,880 --> 01:31:59,030
l guess you liked him, didn't you?

925
01:32:00,200 --> 01:32:02,156
I guess everybody did.

926
01:32:04,200 --> 01:32:07,317
Well, l'll tell you,
it was different with me.

927
01:32:07,640 --> 01:32:08,993
l loved him.

928
01:32:10,600 --> 01:32:12,431
He loved me too.

929
01:32:17,880 --> 01:32:19,552
Are you the one he'd take swimming...

930
01:32:20,160 --> 01:32:21,434
...out at the tank?

931
01:32:21,680 --> 01:32:23,636
He told you about that?

932
01:32:24,960 --> 01:32:26,393
Yeah, l was the one.

933
01:32:29,880 --> 01:32:32,553
l guess if it wasn't for Sam...

934
01:32:32,840 --> 01:32:36,196
...l'd just about have missed it.
Whatever it is.

935
01:32:37,800 --> 01:32:40,917
l'd have been one of them
amity types that thinks...

936
01:32:41,200 --> 01:32:44,670
...that playing bridge is
the best thing that life has to offer.

937
01:32:52,160 --> 01:32:54,116
Old Sam the Lion.

938
01:32:57,000 --> 01:33:00,913
Nobody knows where he got that name.
l gave it to him.

939
01:33:01,600 --> 01:33:02,828
One night...

940
01:33:03,320 --> 01:33:05,470
...itjust came to me.

941
01:33:09,560 --> 01:33:11,471
He was so pleased.

942
01:33:14,880 --> 01:33:17,189
l was 22 years old then.

943
01:33:18,560 --> 01:33:19,993
Can you imagine?

944
01:33:24,080 --> 01:33:25,115
lt's terrible...

945
01:33:25,400 --> 01:33:29,109
...to only meet one man in life
that knows what you're worth.

946
01:33:30,800 --> 01:33:31,789
Just terrible.

947
01:33:34,920 --> 01:33:36,319
l've looked too.

948
01:33:38,040 --> 01:33:40,315
You wouldn't believe
how l've looked.

949
01:33:44,920 --> 01:33:47,912
Well, now l know why Sam liked you.

950
01:33:48,200 --> 01:33:49,110
Loved me.

951
01:33:49,360 --> 01:33:50,679
Loved you, l mean.

952
01:33:51,800 --> 01:33:53,074
Do you?

953
01:33:54,520 --> 01:33:57,159
l can kind of see
what he saw in you too.

954
01:34:06,240 --> 01:34:08,310
Nope. l'll just go on home.

955
01:34:08,680 --> 01:34:09,908
Go on. Get out.

956
01:34:14,240 --> 01:34:17,312
Think l could learn to drink?

957
01:34:23,640 --> 01:34:26,154
You might.
Better keep on practising.

958
01:34:55,280 --> 01:34:57,430
That Logan boy's a quarterback,
ain't he?

959
01:34:57,720 --> 01:35:00,029
Boy, we've fnally got us a team!

960
01:35:00,400 --> 01:35:02,356
Didn't back in your day, did they?

961
01:35:02,720 --> 01:35:04,119
No, we wasn't much good.

962
01:35:04,480 --> 01:35:06,391
You just never learned
the fundamentals.

963
01:35:06,720 --> 01:35:09,188
You know, blocking and tackling.

964
01:35:09,520 --> 01:35:10,953
Not like this team.

965
01:35:11,240 --> 01:35:13,390
When was it you graduated?
Last year.

966
01:35:13,680 --> 01:35:14,669
You don't mean it.

967
01:35:14,960 --> 01:35:17,997
Seems longer than that
since you and Duane played ball.

968
01:35:18,280 --> 01:35:19,633
l seen Duane a while ago.

969
01:35:19,920 --> 01:35:22,195
He's home on leave,
wearing his uniform.

970
01:35:22,480 --> 01:35:24,311
l ain't seen him yet.

971
01:35:29,720 --> 01:35:31,312
How are you, Chester?
Fine, coach.

972
01:35:31,600 --> 01:35:34,592
See if we can't stretch
that goddamn thing a little.

973
01:35:34,960 --> 01:35:38,839
You know a man never ought to cheat,
unless it's for a good cause.

974
01:35:40,080 --> 01:35:41,877
He's a good old boy, ain't he?

975
01:35:46,720 --> 01:35:51,396
Anarene High School
We love you

976
01:35:51,640 --> 01:35:54,950
Love you
Oh so grand

977
01:35:56,520 --> 01:36:01,389
We will always be so loyal

978
01:36:01,640 --> 01:36:05,519
Loyal to a man

979
01:36:06,240 --> 01:36:10,438
Whether in defeat or victory

980
01:36:10,680 --> 01:36:12,989
We will e'er be true

981
01:36:32,440 --> 01:36:33,839
Hi, Mrs. Jackson.

982
01:36:34,200 --> 01:36:35,110
Duane here?

983
01:36:35,480 --> 01:36:39,359
That's his car out there, ain't it?
He's here if he ain't walked off.

984
01:36:47,080 --> 01:36:48,433
Hi, how you been?

985
01:36:49,040 --> 01:36:50,473
Pretty good.

986
01:36:53,080 --> 01:36:55,548
l been thinking all week
that l'd run into you.

987
01:36:58,240 --> 01:36:59,832
l heard you was going off to Korea.

988
01:37:00,120 --> 01:37:02,918
Thought l'd get over here
and see you before you got off.

989
01:37:03,960 --> 01:37:06,918
Glad you did.
l'm taking the bus in the morning.

990
01:37:14,320 --> 01:37:15,548
Want to go to the picture show?

991
01:37:16,440 --> 01:37:18,829
Miss Mosey has to close it.
Tonight's the last night.

992
01:37:19,360 --> 01:37:21,112
Yeah, might as well go.

993
01:37:21,400 --> 01:37:24,198
Hate to miss the last night.
Take the Mercury.

994
01:37:24,600 --> 01:37:26,909
Be the last chance l'll have
to drive it for a while.

995
01:37:33,080 --> 01:37:34,399
Ready, Matthew?

996
01:37:34,640 --> 01:37:35,390
All ready.

997
